<h1 style="margin-bottom:0px;">Reconfigure Ingress Controller</h1><div class="f14 metric" style="color:#656668;display:flex;"><img src="/assets/images/calendar.png" style="height:12px;margin-top:auto;margin-bottom:auto;"><span class="updateDate">&nbsp; Updated on 26/06/2019</span> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <img src="/assets/images/updated.png" style="height:12px;margin-top:auto;margin-bottom:auto;"><span class="readTime">&nbsp; 28 seconds to read</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><br><div class="mw-parser-output"><p>You need to reconfigure Ingress controller to accommodate the long hostname length on AWS. Follow the steps:
</p>
<ol><li>Run the following command:
<pre>kubectl edit cm ingress-controller-config -n opsbridge-&lt;id&gt;</pre>
</li><li>Edit the <code>configmap</code> and insert the following data:
<pre>map-hash-bucket-size: "64"
server-name-hash-bucket-size: "128"</pre>
</li><li>Save the file.</li>
<li>Delete the <code>ingress-controller</code> pod by running the following command:
<pre>kubectl delete pod ingress-controller-&lt;ID&gt; -n opsbridge-&lt;id&gt;</pre>
</li><li>Wait until the pod is recreated and running again.</li></ol>

